<div id="column3" class="box box_scroll">
<H1>Triatholon Events</H1>
<ul>
  <li>
<strong>Ironman Triathlons </strong>
  <li><img src="images/logos/logo_ironman.jpg" width="80" height="24" hspace="3" vspace="3" align="left" /><a href="http://ironman.com/" target="newwindow">IronMan </a> The official site of Ironman racing series, including the World Championship in Hawaii. Some history, training tips, news and the skinny on where to go to qualify for the greatest race of all.
  <li><a href="http://www.ironmanoz.com/" target="newwindow">Ironman Australia</a> Ironman race held in Forster-Tuncurry, New South Wales.
  <li><img src="images/logos/logo_ironman_brazil.jpg" width="100" height="108" align="right" /><a href="http://www.ironmanbrazil.com/" target="newwindow"> Ironman Brazil</a>  Description of the course, history, map, photo album, event structure, register online and email addresses to the organization of the event.
  <li><a href="http://www.ironman.ca/" target="newwindow">Ironman Canada</a> Annual Ironman distance triathlon held in Penticton, British Columbia.
  <li><a href="http://www.ironman.co.nz/" target="newwindow">Ironman New Zealand</a> Annual event on the shores of Lake Taupo. Current event information and registration, along with archive of past events.
  <li><a href="http://www.ironman.ch/" target="newwindow">Ironman Switzerland</a> Referred to as Euroman. Features date/time, registration, course details, and contacts.
  <li><a href="http://www.ironman.de/" target="newwindow">Ironman Triathlon Germany</a> Held in August in Frankfurt. Offers registration, competitors list, time schedule, race courses, FAQs, race hotel information, and links.
  <li><a href="http://www.ironmanwisconsin.com/" target="newwindow">Ironman Wisconsin</a> Held in Madison. Features updates, course details, registration information, discussion forum, volunteer and participant information and news, merchandise, and contacts.
  <li>
<strong>  Triathlons</strong>
<li><a href="http://www.loaring.com/loaring/triathlon.htm" target="newwindow"> Loaring Triathlon</a> Offers a triathlon and double triathlon (same three events performed back-to-back) at Colchester South Township, Ontario. Images, course details, results archive and registration featured.
<li><a href="http://www.wi.ca/peach/" target="newwindow">Peach Classic Triathlon</a> Held in July in Penticton, BC, an Olympic distance triathlon.  1.5 km swim, 40 km bike, and 10 km run.
<li><a href="http://www.trisportcanada.com" target="newwindow">Subaru Triathlon Series</a> The world's largest triathlon series in Ontario.
<li><a href="http://www.thelondontriathlon.com" target="newwindow"> The London Triathlon</a> Open to all ability levels. Provides merchandise, a photo gallery, past results, contacts, registration details, and charity information.
<li><a href="http://www.trifind.com/" target="newwindow"> The American Triathlon Calendar</a> Listing of triathlon and multisport events, local and worldwide. Updated daily.
<li><a href="http://www.scenesofvermont.com/smugglers/event.htm" target="newwindow"> Annual Smug-a-thon</a> A in Jeffersonville, Vermont event; a day of fun at the Smug-a-Thon with a 3-mile jog or walk, a 4-mile downstream paddle, and a 9.5 mile bike ride. Open to competitive and non-competitive individuals or teams.
<li><a href="http://www.bfasracing.org/" target="newwindow">Beaches Fine Arts Series Triathlon</a> - Annual USAT-sanctioned triathlon series held in May, June and July each year. The sprint triathlon includes a beach swim, flat bike and run.
<li><a href="http://www.buffalospringslaketriathlon.com/" target="newwindow">Buffalo Springs Lake Triathlon</a> Schedule and registration information and previous year's results for sprint tri-raider and half-ironman.  Located near Lubbock, Texas.
<li><a href="http://www.captextri.com/" target="newwindow">Capital of Texas Triathlon</a> Austin, Texas. Course map, registration information, fees, and awards.
<li><a href="http://elkharttriathlons.activecm.net" target="newwindow">Elkhart Lake Multisports</a> Sponsors of a variety of triathlon and duathlon events in Elkhart Lake, Wisconsin.  Site provides race information and results, course maps, registration.
<li><a href="http://www.envirosports.com/" target="newwindow">Envirosports</a> San Francisco Bay Area organizers of all sorts multisport events, including the Alcatraz Sharkfest swim and the original Escape from Alcatraz triathlon.
<li><a href="http://www.thegreatrace.org/" target="newwindow">Eppie's Great Race</a> Annual multisport events held in July in Sacramento, California.
<li><a href="http://www.joshbillings.com/" target="newwindow">Great Josh Billings RunAground Triathlon</a> Located in Great Barrington, Massachusetts with an event description, volunteer opportunities, race results and an application.
<li><a href="http://www.hammermantriathlon.com/" target="newwindow">XTERRA Hammerman Triathlon</a> Information and registration for this 1.0 mile swim, 10.9 mile bike, 3.1 mile run course held in Anchorage, Alaska. Also, men, women and team divisions along with photo gallery and results archive.
<li><a href="http://www.timeoutproductions.com/" target="newwindow">New England Triathlon Series</a> For over 15 years, Time Out! Productions presents this series of multisport events.
<li><a href="http://www.pleasantprairietriathlon.com/" target="newwindow">Pleasant Prairie Triathlon</a> Pleasant Prairie, Wisconsin.  A sanctioned USAT event with a 1.5 K swim, 40 K bike and 10 K run. Kids triathlon occurs one day earlier.
<li><a href="http://www.tbfracing.com/" target="newwindow">TBF Racing Adventurous Multi-Sport Events</a> Offers Olympic distance and Sprint Triathlons, Duathlons,  and Mt Bike Racing events.
<li><a href="">Laguna Phuket Triathlon</a> Annual event held in November in southern Thailand. Includes information on registration deadline and forms, race results archive, photo gallery, course and contacts.
<li><a href="http://www.rev3tri.com/" target="newwindow">REVOLUTION3</a> The REVOLUTION3 Triathlon is focused on offering a fun, first class race experience.
</li>
</ul>
